An unexpected but deliciously nostalgic hash tag, #jesuisvieux, has been
trending on the French speaking social media scene. Since July 26th, twitter
users have been going down memory lane, posting tweets relating their memories
from youth with the hash tag
[#jesuisvieux](http://twitter.com/#search?q=%23jesuisvieux) ( I am old – men)
or [#jesuisvieille ](http://twitter.com/#search?q=%23jesuisvieille)( I am old
– women). The timeline for the hashtag was filled with often humorous,
sometimes sweet updates and provides a good snapshot of the evolution of
information technology usage and its demographics.  
It is unclear whether the article in the New York Times on July 15 entitled:
“[Aging Gracefully, the French
Way](http://www.nytimes.com/2010/07/15/fashion/15French.html)” has anything to
do with the twitter trend but aging is certainly on a lot of people's mind in
the francophone world and they seemingly embrace it openly.  
A few newspapers have collected and curated the best of them. Here is an
article by Coline Bérard at L'Express.fr: “[Twitter c'est pour les
vieux”](http://www.lexpress.fr/actualite/societe/twitter-c-est-pour-les-
vieux_908960.html), (twitter is for old people in English) and Belgian
newspaper [Le Soir](http://Soir.be) is currently posting and monitoring a
[live blogging session
](http://www.coveritlive.com/index2.php/option=com_altcaster/task=viewaltcast/altcast_code=d210292f64/height=1200/width=480)about
the #Jesuisvieux hashtag on the Cover It Live platform.

[![](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/jesuisvieux-
trendmap-375x234.jpg)](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2010/07/jesuisvieux-trendmap.jpg)

Screenshot of the #Jesuistropvieux tag on Trendsmap.com

According to Hashtags.org, #jesuisvieux hash tag made up to [0.03% of tweets
worldwide](http://hashtags.org/jesuisvieux) on July 27.  
Here are a few tweets that have caught out attention:

From [@JocelyneRobert](http://twitter.com/JocelyneRobert) in Montréal, Canada:

> On ne brimait pas nos élans sexuels avec la menace des ITS mais avec la
> menace de l'enfer
> [**#jesuisvieille**](http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23jesuisvieille)

We did not suppress our libido with the threat of STDs but with the the threat
of hell #IamOld

[Pierre Côté](http://twitter.com/pierrecote):

> J'ai surfé sur le WWW en utilisant NETSCAPE #jesuisvieux

I surfed the web using Netscape

[Anna Gueye](http://twitter.com/annagueye) from Senegal and La Hague, Holland:

> #jesuisvieux il y avait des 1ères classes dans le métro #jesuisvieille

There were first class seats in the metro

[slim404](http://twitter.com/%40slim404) in Tunisia:

> Le 7 nov. 1987 j'étais content. Mon père m'a dit : “tu va pas à l'école
> aujourd'hui, on ne sait jamais” #jesuisvieux

On [Nov 7 1987](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zine_El_Abidine_Ben_Ali), my dad
told me:” You are not going to class today, who knows what can happen.

[@bravepatrie:](http://twitter.com/bravepatrie)

> J'ai vu des ministres démissionner quand ils étaient mis en cause dans des
> affaires. #jesuisvieux

Ministers actually resigned when they were implicated in scandals

[Necessepas](http://twitter.com/necessepas):

> J'ai été amoureuse d'Albator #jesuisvieille http://youtu.be/SpE9Yo9dmIo

I was in love with [Captain
Harlock](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Captain_Harlock)
http://youtu.be/SpE9Yo9dmIo

[Boris:](http://twitter.com/ras_bo)

> Je me souviens avoir vu la comète de Halley #jesuisvieux

I remember seeing Halley's comet

[sophiedurocher](http://twitter.com/sophiedurocher):

> Dans ma jeunesse, il n'y avait pas Internet pour que des anonymes qui n'ont
> pas de vie déversent leur haine et leur mépris. #jesuisvieille

When I was young, There was no internet for no-life anonymous people to pour
down their hatred and comtempt

[Dugomo](twitter.com/Dugomo):

> Voler des 33 tours, c'était quand même plus héroïque que télécharger
> #jesuisvieux

Stealing LP records took more guts than downloading songs

[Kristalynm9](http://twitter.com/kristalynm9):

> J'ai déjà imprimer un travail de Cégep sur une imprimante a ruban de
> Commodore 64 a @tremblay96 #jesuisvieux

I did a print job for CEGEP on a Commodore 64 printer in @tremblay96

[fastclemmy:](http://twitter.com/fastclemmy)

> on est tous le vieux de quelqu'un #jesuisvieux

We all are someone else's elder

